---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="C3 Alliance" description="The Cosmic Commons Communities Alliance - Cooperative infrastructure for sovereign communities">
  <section class="c3">
    <div class="c3__hero">
      <div class="c3__hero-container container">
        <span class="c3__eyebrow">Cosmic Commons Communities</span>
        <h1 class="c3__title text-balance">C3 Alliance</h1>
        <p class="c3__subtitle">
          Cooperative infrastructure for sovereign communities
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="c3__content container container--prose">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>What is the C3 Alliance?</h2>
        <p>
          The <strong>C3 Alliance</strong> (Cosmic Commons Communities Alliance) is a network 
          of cooperatives, community land trusts, and sovereign communities building shared 
          infrastructure for the cooperative economy.
        </p>
        <p>
          We believe in coordination without coercion, value creation without extraction, 
          and governance without centralized authority. The Alliance provides the technical, 
          legal, and social infrastructure to make this possible.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Core Infrastructure</h2>
        
        <h3>Governance Frameworks</h3>
        <p>
          Tokenized governance systems that enable transparent, participatory decision-making 
          across distributed communities. Our governance infrastructure includes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>SBT-DID (Soulbound Token Decentralized Identity) for member verification</li>
          <li>COMM tokens for governance participation</li>
          <li>On-chain proposal and voting mechanisms</li>
          <li>Treasury management for shared resources</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>N3 Commons Nodes</h3>
        <p>
          Physical infrastructure nodes that combine:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Renewable energy production (solar, wind)</li>
          <li>Sustainable food systems (permaculture, aquaponics)</li>
          <li>Community gathering and workspace</li>
          <li>Local economic infrastructure</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The first N3 Commons node is currently being developed in Hardin County, Texas.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Shared Technology</h3>
        <p>
          Open-source infrastructure for cooperative operations:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Blockchain-based accounting and treasury</li>
          <li>Member coordination tools</li>
          <li>Federated communication systems</li>
          <li>Shared knowledge repositories</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Exit-to-Cooperative (E2C)</h2>
        <p>
          One of our key initiatives is helping traditional businesses convert to 
          cooperative ownership structures. E2C provides:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Legal framework templates</li>
          <li>Tokenomics design for ownership transition</li>
          <li>Governance migration strategies</li>
          <li>Ongoing support and integration into the Alliance</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Tokenomics</h2>
        <p>
          The C3 Alliance operates on a multi-token system:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>COMM</strong> - Governance token for Alliance-wide decisions</li>
          <li><strong>PPT</strong> - Plausible Potentials service credits</li>
          <li><strong>XPT</strong> - Experience tokens tracking contribution and reputation</li>
          <li><strong>Member-specific tokens</strong> - For local cooperative governance</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Membership</h2>
        <p>
          The C3 Alliance is open to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Existing cooperatives seeking shared infrastructure</li>
          <li>Communities exploring cooperative models</li>
          <li>Businesses considering Exit-to-Cooperative transition</li>
          <li>Individuals aligned with cooperative principles</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          For membership inquiries, contact us at{' '}
          <a href="mailto:alliance@c3alliance.org">alliance@c3alliance.org</a>
        </p>
        
        <h2>Learn More</h2>
        <p>
          Stay updated on C3 Alliance developments through this Voice publication. 
          Key topics we cover:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/posts/category/c3-alliance">C3 Alliance Updates</a></li>
          <li><a href="/posts/category/cooperative-economics">Cooperative Economics</a></li>
          <li><a href="/posts/category/blockchain-governance">Blockchain Governance</a></li>
          <li><a href="/posts/category/sovereignty">Sovereignty</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .c3__hero {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--purple-dark) 0%,
      var(--purple) 50%,
      var(--royal-blue-dark) 100%
    );
    color: var(--white);
    padding: var(--space-20) 0 var(--space-16);
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .c3__eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  .c3__title {
    font-size: var(--text-5xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--white);
  }
  
  .c3__subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--gray-200);
    max-width: 50ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .c3__content {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-24);
  }
  
  .c3__content h2 {
    color: var(--royal-blue);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
  }
  
  .c3__content h3 {
    color: var(--purple);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }
  
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .c3__content h2 {
      color: var(--gold);
    }
    
    .c3__content h3 {
      color: var(--gold-light);
    }
  }
</style>
